This code simply displays the time and date.

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<body>

<h2>My First JavaScript</h2>

<button type="button"
onclick="document.getElementById('demo').innerHTML = Date()">
Know Date and Time.</button>

<p id="demo"></p>

</body>
</html> 

OUTPUT

My First JavaScript
Know Date and Time.        !this is displayed inside a button.
Wed Feb 26 2020 09:57:05 GMT+0530 (India Standard Time)
